        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 21 at 12:36AM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 1236 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Caddo Valley, or 7 miles northeast of Arkadelphia, moving southwest
at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Arkadelphia...                    Caddo Valley...
Gum Springs in Clark County...    Richwoods...
DeGray Lake State Park...         Donaldson...
Friendship...                     Lower Lake Recreation Area...
Curtis...                         Hollywood...
De Roche...                       Midway in Hot Spring County...
Joan...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
